09/02/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Justice Minister Meri Mladenovska-Gjorgjievska met on Tuesday (8 February) with representatives of the parliamentary parties, briefing them on the pace of preparations for the 13 March municipal elections. 
Lists of eligible voters are being printed, and the justice ministry has begun submitting relevant regulations to municipal election committees. 
The Macedonian civil association MOST plans to deploy 3,500 local observers.
Also Tuesday, the government adopted a draft law on crisis management and forwarded it to parliament. 
The bill, more than a year in the works, was prepared in line with EU and NATO standards. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 09/02/05; A1 TV - 08/02/05)
